{/*
    ContentPanel is intentionally a passthrough. Starlight calls this
    component multiple times per page (hero / title / content / footer
    blocks) and its default adds padding + a max-width container + a
    divider between successive panels. Our framing lives elsewhere:

      - TwoColumnContent owns the page-level grid + padding
      - PageTitle owns the title block padding + actions row
      - MarkdownContent owns prose width + typography
      - Pagination + Footer own the trailing block

    Wrapping content here would double-pad and fight those overrides.
    The structural `content-panel` class is preserved so any third-party
    CSS or future tooling that targets it still works, but the layout
    rules attached to it in Starlight core are deliberately not carried
    over. If you find yourself wanting padding or a divider here, add
    it to the inner component (PageTitle / MarkdownContent / Footer)
    instead — that's where the design system's framing lives.
*/}
<div class="content-panel">
    <slot />
</div>

<style>
    /* No padding, no max-width, no divider rules — see comment above.
     * The class exists for selector stability only. */
    .content-panel {
        display: contents;
    }
</style>
